OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Sheep Creek below Spring in Bryce Canyon National Park
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Sheep Creek below a spring in Bryce Canyon National Park. This site is downstream from an unnamed spring, and just upstream of the confluence of Sheep Creek with Short Canyon. Latitude and longitude coordinates were compiled from previous studies or topographic map interpolation. This station has an additional ID from Utah Dept. of Environmental Quality of 4951855 with a station name of Sheep Ck bl Spring in Bryce Cyn NP.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Yellow Creek below Spring in Bryce Canyon National Park
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Yellow Creek below spring in Bryce Canyon National Park. The site is approximately 3.1 kilometers downstream of Yellow Spring. Latitude and longitude coordinates were compiled from previous studies or topographic map interpolation. This station has additional IDs and station names: USGS-NWIS Site No. 373428112082801, Yellow Ck bl Spring in Bryce Cyn NP; and Utah Dept. of Environmental Quality 4951857, Yellow Ck bl Spring in Bryce Cyn NP.

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationName: Mossy Cave Spring Northwest of Tropic
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This station is at Mossy Cave Spring, northwest of Tropic, Utah. Mossy Cave Spring is in Water Canyon, river right, approximately 450 meters upstream of the confluence of Water Canyon with Tropic Canyon. Latitude and longitude coordinates were compiled from previous studies or topographic map interpolation. This station has an additional ID from Utah Dept. of Environmental Quality of 4951915 with a station name of Mossy Cave Spring NW of Tropic.
